The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 TIL net profit up to Rs 19 cr

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, June 5: TIL Ltd has reported an 88 per cent rise in profit before tax for 2005-06 at Rs 18.85 crore, compared with Rs 10.04 crore in the previous fiscal. The board has recommended a 20 per cent dividend for shareholders, compared with 12.5 per cent in the previous fiscal.

 The board also decided to insert a few clauses in the memorandum of association of the company to facilitate the exploration of new business opportunities allied with its core operating business. The board had earlier decided to pass the resolution through postal ballot and had appointed AK Labh amp; Co as the scrutiniser for the postal ballot. 

 TIL provides equipment for infrastructure development, such as material handling, earthmoving, mining, construction and power systems. The company started selling electric level luffing cranes since last fiscal, and will continue to introduce sophisticated container and cargo handling equipment catering to the growing demand from the infrastructure sector, a release said. 

 The companys total income during the last quarter of 2005-06 increased 32 per cent to Rs 155.14 crore from Rs 117.68 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year. 




